sql:
SELECT model 
FROM compressors 
WHERE working_pressure > 10;

SELECT COUNT(compressor_id)
FROM compressors
WHERE working_pressure > 10;

external_knowledge:
The phrase "put into operation" refers to compressors that have a recorded `commissioning_date`; "machines" refers to compressor instances; "location" is synonymous with `site_id`.;
The count of machines is the total number of compressor instances commissioned at each site. ;
All compressor instances must have a commissioning date to be counted. ;

sql:
SELECT site_id, COUNT(compressor_id) AS total_compressors
FROM compressor_instances
GROUP BY site_id;

SELECT COUNT(compressor_id) AS total_compressors, model, working_pressure
FROM compressors
GROUP BY model, working_pressure;

SELECT compressor_id, model, working_pressure, AVG(nominal_motor_output) AS avg_nominal_motor_output
FROM compressors
GROUP BY compressor_id, model, working_pressure;

SELECT site_name
FROM sites
WHERE site_id = 1;
